The paper deals with the problem of stabilizing an unstable plant over a noisy communication link, which is a key issue in networked control systems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the theoretical framework of tree codes and their practical implementation, which could fall under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses novel sufficient conditions to analyze the rate and reliability of tree codes, which could be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
